The paper deals with an online scheduling problem, which is a classic topic in computer science and falls under the category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The problem involves maximizing the number of jobs completed before their deadline, which is related to game theory (cs.GT) and optimization (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the competitive ratio of the algorithm, which is a measure of its performance, and involves information theory (cs.IT) and control theory (cs.SY).
